Blocks.Text: 1 traditional statistical machine learning model: Conditional Random Field (CRF)
6 neural network models from a combination of
(1) A BiLSTM for word-level feature extraction
(2) CRF or non-CRF as the inference layer or (3) without character information or encoding
character feature with structure CNN, LSTM (denoted as CCNN and CLSTM respectively)
3 general domain PLM including BERT, RoBERTa and BART
All the experiments of NER models are conducted using NCRF+ (Yang and Zhang, 2018)
Hyperparameters of the models are default settings from Yang et al. (2018a).
We reported the results based on experiments on 5 different random seeds: 22, 32, 42, 52 and 62.
